display_name: IDQA Step Check (0 = check not performed; 1 = passed check; -1 = failed check)
what_it_actually_means:
Outlier detection for abrupt step changes (spikes) was done using a rolling median (moving median) algorithm with a window of size three, advancing one
data point for each computation and a threshold of 0.006, i.e. if the difference between the original data point and its corresponding median is greater 
than 0.006 the data point is filtered out of the data set.
